Sentencas: Y0.8Ca0.2BaCo4O7 (+) (delta) (YCBC4) was synthesized and investigated as a cathode for proton-conducting intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: A promising cathode for proton-conducting intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells: Y0.8Ca0.2BaCo4O7 + δ

Sentencas: Low thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) (similar to 9.9 x 10(-6) K-1) can provide good thermal expansion compatibility with the standard SOFC electrolyte materials.
Titulo: A promising cathode for proton-conducting intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells: Y0.8Ca0.2BaCo4O7 + δ

Sentencas: Laboratory-sized quad-layer cells, consisting of NiO-BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY)/NiO-BZCY/BZCY/YCBC4, were fabricated by a one-step dry-pressing/co-firing process and tested from 550 to 700 degrees C with humidified hydrogen (similar to 3% H2O) as the fuel and static air as the oxidant, respectively.
Titulo: A promising cathode for proton-conducting intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells: Y0.8Ca0.2BaCo4O7 + δ

Sentencas: An excellent power density of 472 mW cm(-2) and a low electrode polarization resistance of 0.121 Omega cm(2) were obtained at 700 degrees C. Preliminary results demonstrated that the YCBC4 can be a promising cathode material for proton-conducting IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: A promising cathode for proton-conducting intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells: Y0.8Ca0.2BaCo4O7 + δ
